# Hot Sales — agent lane

**Read first:** [docs/hot-sales/RUNTIME.md](docs/hot-sales/RUNTIME.md) · Index: [docs/hot-sales/README.md](docs/hot-sales/README.md)

## Phase state

Phase 2A **implementation + ops closed** (2026-07-10). Gates 1–7 complete. Production `HOT_SALES_RBAC_ENABLED=true`.

## Forbidden without explicit user approval

- Phase **2B, 2C, 2D** (finance, pickup, Excel, notifications, ERP)
- New Hot Sales permissions, roles, RBAC UI, schema migrations, or trade features
- Disabling production RBAC except documented rollback in RUNTIME.md
- Repo normalization mixed into Hot Sales commits
- Guardian Auth / portal atmosphere framed as Hot Sales work

## Allowed

- Production-blocking emergency fixes on frozen boundary (merge to `main`, redeploy)
- Test-lane commits separate from unrelated refactors

## Test identity (do not conflate)

- `SHARED_ADMIN_EMAIL` — admin matrix, not sales allowlist
- `PREVIEW_CLIENT_EMAIL` — not auto-seeded into `hot_sales_sales_member`
- Redirect to `/client` for non-allowlisted `/trade` users is **expected**

## Before coding

If the task is not a production-blocking fix — **stop and ask** whether scope reopened. Depth: [ops/gate-register.md](docs/hot-sales/ops/gate-register.md).
